{
  "texts": [
    "To address the issue of limited data and to reduce computational cost, they fine-tuned the weights of the models.",
    "Additionally, affine transform techniques were employed for data augmentation.",
    "The results revealed that the ResNet50 model achieved the highest accuracy rates, reaching 99.49% for ischemia and 84.76% for infection detection.",
    "Traditional machine learning techniques have also found significant use in wound image classification.",
    "Yadav et al."
  ]
}